-- Nomura Holdings Hires Paul Lejuez of Credit Suisse as U.S. Retail Analyst
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-07-13T18:27:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/nomura-holdings-hires-paul-lejuez-of-credit-suisse-as-u-s-retail-analyst.html

          
          
             Nomura Holdings Inc. , Japan’s
biggest brokerage, hired  Paul Lejuez  of Credit Suisse Group AG
as an analyst covering U.S. retail companies.  
 Lejuez will join the company’s U.S. unit, Nomura Securities
International Inc., as a senior analyst covering retailers, the
Tokyo-based company said in a statement today. Lejuez will be
based in New York and report to  Michael Rietbrock , head of U.S.
equity research, the statement said.  
 Jonathan Hodgkinson , a Nomura spokesman in New York,
confirmed the statement.  
